MinepanelModern Minecraft Server Management

Manage multiple Minecraft servers with a beautiful web interface using Docker

Get Started
View on GitHub
Docker Hub
🚀

Quick Deployment

One-command deployment from Docker Hub. Get your server panel running in seconds.

🎨

Modern Interface

Beautiful and intuitive web interface built with Next.js and React.

🐳

Docker Native

Each server runs in its own isolated container for better performance and security.

📊

Real-time Monitoring

Monitor CPU, RAM usage and view logs in real-time with error detection.

🔧

Full Control

Manage all server types - Vanilla, Paper, Forge, Fabric, Spigot, Purpur, and more.

📁

File Browser

Integrated file browser for easy config editing and server management.

💾

Automatic Backups

Built-in backup system to keep your worlds safe.

🌍

Multi-language

Available in English and Spanish, with more languages coming soon.

🔄

Multi-architecture

Works on Intel/AMD, ARM, Raspberry Pi, and Apple Silicon.

Why Minepanel? ​

After trying several server management solutions, I wanted something that was:

  • ✨ Easy to use - No complex configurations
  • 🎨 Modern interface - Built with Next.js
  • 🚀 Quick to deploy - One command installation
  • 💪 Powerful - Manage multiple servers effortlessly

Quick Start ​

Get up and running in less than 2 minutes:

bash
# Create docker-compose.yml file, then:
mkdir -p servers filebrowser-data
docker compose up -d
1
2
3

Access the panel at http://localhost:3000

Default Credentials

Username: admin | Password: admin (change after first login!)

Built On ​

  • Frontend: Next.js + React + TypeScript
  • Backend: NestJS
  • Minecraft Servers: itzg/docker-minecraft-server
  • Backups: itzg/docker-mc-backup
  • File Browser: Filebrowser
